comments.body:
@edsantiago the goal of rootless_storage_path is for systems that have NFS homedirs and can't run with the default storage.conf that we create in the homedir.  IE $HOME/.local/share/containers/storage will not work. 

We want to allow administrators to tell podman/buildah to create their content in /var/tmp for example. 

Imagine a university with nfs homedirs, admin could set this up and every student logging in would automatically have their first podman work rather then fail, and force every student to edit the storage.conf that was generated in the homedir
